f=Engineering/quinn/custom/browser-verification/SKILL.md · in=browser-verification quinn's evidence layer department's founding problem: **agents say "done"; browsers tell truth.** Two gates, two tools. **edit gate** (Reticle, MCP) verifies frontend edit actually took effect real state, real network calls, `file:line` traceability catching mock data half-wired edit time. **release gate** (Playwright, imported webapp-testing skill) runs critical user flows real browser before anything ships E2E tier test-strategy's matrix requires. · p=Reticle-era lesson (dev's delivery-governance cites too): agent reports "feature complete" page shell placeholder data dead buttons. Static review can't catch code *looks* wired. browser executing real app proves claim. skill makes browser evidence gate requirement, nice-to-have: evidence, pass. · wu=Triggers: "verify edit," "did change actually render," "run browser checks," "E2E release," "browser evidence," any mia/frontend diff review time (edit gate), release user-facing changes (release gate, matrix's tier). · st:/ Protocol=`EDIT GATE (per frontend change — Reticle when connected) \· Frontend diff claims done \· -> Verify in the running app: element exists \· state real (no mock/fixture leakage) \· \· expected network calls fire \· change traces to file:line \· -> PASS: evidence attached to the review \· FAIL: specific delta back to author` · in=**Evidence didn't happen.** verification verdict carries artifacts: screenshots, console/network excerpts, `file:line` traces (edit gate). checked works" without artifacts verdict it's exact claim skill exists distrust. **Edit gate frontend diff.** Element rendered, real data bound (fixture/mock values leaking DOM integrity block dev's checklist §0), expected network calls fired, new console errors. Route evidence review. **Release gate critical flows.** `critical_flows` list operator-set config (rule 0.5 quinn doesn't decide what's business-critical). Run flow webapp-testing machinery: real browser, headless, `networkidle` before inspection, assertions outcomes page loads. **Flaky browser tests follow flaky rule.** flow passes retry goes regression-map's flaky register quarantined, counted, owned never silently retried-until-green gate. **Degrade loudly without connectors.** Reticle edit gate labeled manual checklist (same checks, human-or-agent-executed, flagged "unverified tooling"). Playwright release gate's tier marked UNMET, test-strategy's verdict says so; gate quietly shrink. **Charter compliance.** Browser runs external tool calls: plan-locked, sandboxed, egress-allowlisted. Test data synthetic never production data test browser (Rail 2's spirit; production data handling belongs dana under Rail discipline). · of=`## Browser Evidence: [change/release] — gate: EDIT / RELEASE \· Checks run: [list] \· Evidence: [screenshot/log/trace refs] \· Mock-data leakage: [none / found → integrity block] \· Flows: [flow \· PASS/FAIL \· artifact] \· ` · pr=**Agents claim; browsers prove** browser evidence, E-tier pass., **Verdicts carry artifacts** screenshots logs, assurances., **Mock data DOM integrity block**, cosmetic note., **Degradation loud** missing tool shrinks capability, never silently shrinks gate., **Critical flows operator-defined** quinn enforces list, doesn't author (rule 0.5)., **Test runs charter-bound** plan-locked, sandboxed, synthetic data only. · f=Neither tool connected gates run labeled manual checklists; verdict carries "unverified tooling" flag; connector adoption surfaced operator (§5 redesign plan)., App can't run headless needs real devices note limitation, verify what's verifiable, flag rest; mobile-specific verification nova's domain built., Flow fails CI, locally environment delta itself finding (candidate map entry), reason pass. · b:with Other Skills=**marketplace/webapp-testing** (imported, verbatim) Playwright machinery; skill decides what verify, gates, what passes improvements here, never verbatim import., **test-strategy** (sibling) owns gate verdict; supplies E-tier edit-gate evidence feeding it., **regression-map** (sibling) receives flaky browser flows environment-delta findings., **mia** (frontend, built) primary producer edit-gate work; Agentation feedback loop planned mia upstream authoring context, substitute verification., **charter-enforcement** (sibling) locks sandboxes browser runs themselves.